snippet.textDisplay:
I've been in their position!

It's impatience which initially rushes you to put your vision in motion because you think everything will fall in place automatically, which leads to taking shortcuts. Naivety plays a big factor in skipping vital steps E.g. not doing market research because you think there already is a demand for a product/service.

You fail because physically and socially you are not up for the challenge of overseeing that vision and making it a reality.

Those 2 ladies took shortcuts and fell short in terms of the physical aspect required to make their vision a reality.
